Claudia Alexandra Madriz Meza was born on June 24, 1987 in San Jose, California, to Mexican parents.
During her younger years, Claudia was exposed to mariachi music on her father's side of the family as both her father and grandfather were mariachi singers.
Claudia attended Mar Vista High School and Mira Mesa Senior High School.
In 2007, Snow released her first compilation album Verbal Assault Vol.1 with many local artists under her label Product Entertainment LLC.
It was followed in 2008 with her first solo mixtape Raising Tha Bar: Tha Mixtape, which included many remixes of popular songs of the era.
In 2009, Verbal Assault Vol. 2 was released, with the single "Whatever It Takes."
In 2010, Snow released Wake Ya Game Up, Vol. 1, along with the Wake Ya Game Up and Woke clothing brands and apparel.
In 2010, Snow released the mixtape Run Up or Shut Up, which was hosted by DJ Ames from the UK and included the hit single "Drunk Love".
On February 16, 2011, the official music video was featured in the popular Latino music television channel Mun2.
Snow then moved her and her family to Texas and performed for two consecutive years at the South by Southwest festival.
On October 26, 2011, Snow released her debut independent album on Street Science Ent.
"Drunk Love" was re-released as a single along with "Woke Wednesday".
